  62      /**
  63       * This method filters a string by replacing special tokens by appropriate values
  64       * and prints it. The corresponding tokens are taken into account:
  65       * - __CAS_VERSION__
  66       * - __PHPCAS_VERSION__
  67       * - __SERVER_BASE_URL__
  68       *
  69       * Used by CAS_Client::PrintHTMLHeader() and CAS_Client::printHTMLFooter().
  70       *
  71       * @param string $str the string to filter and output
  72       *
  73       * @return void
  74       */
  75      private function _htmlFilterOutput($str)
  76      {
  77          $str = str_replace('__CAS_VERSION__', $this->getServerVersion(), $str);
  78          $str = str_replace('__PHPCAS_VERSION__', phpCAS::getVersion(), $str);
  79          $str = str_replace('__SERVER_BASE_URL__', $this->_getServerBaseURL(), $str);
  80          echo $str;
  81      }
  82  
  83      /**
  84       * A string used to print the header of HTML pages. Written by
  85       * CAS_Client::setHTMLHeader(), read by CAS_Client::printHTMLHeader().
  86       *
  87       * @hideinitializer
  88       * @see CAS_Client::setHTMLHeader, CAS_Client::printHTMLHeader()
  89       */
  90      private $_output_header = '';
  91  
  92      /**
  93       * This method prints the header of the HTML output (after filtering). If
  94       * CAS_Client::setHTMLHeader() was not used, a default header is output.
  95       *
  96       * @param string $title the title of the page
  97       *
  98       * @return void
  99       * @see _htmlFilterOutput()
 100       */
 101      public function printHTMLHeader($title)
 102      {
 103          $this->_htmlFilterOutput(
 104              str_replace(
 105                  '__TITLE__', $title,
 106                  (empty($this->_output_header)
 107                  ? '<html><head><title>__TITLE__</title></head><body><h1>__TITLE__</h1>'
 108                  : $this->_output_header)
 109              )
 110          );
 111      }
 112  
 113      /**
 114       * A string used to print the footer of HTML pages. Written by
 115       * CAS_Client::setHTMLFooter(), read by printHTMLFooter().
 116       *
 117       * @hideinitializer
 118       * @see CAS_Client::setHTMLFooter, CAS_Client::printHTMLFooter()
 119       */
 120      private $_output_footer = '';
 121  
 122      /**
 123       * This method prints the footer of the HTML output (after filtering). If
 124       * CAS_Client::setHTMLFooter() was not used, a default footer is output.
 125       *
 126       * @return void
 127       * @see _htmlFilterOutput()
 128       */
 129      public function printHTMLFooter()
 130      {
 131          $lang = $this->getLangObj();
 132          $this->_htmlFilterOutput(
 133              empty($this->_output_footer)?
 134              (phpcas::getVerbose())?
 135                  '<hr><address>phpCAS __PHPCAS_VERSION__ '
 136                  .$lang->getUsingServer()
 137                  .' <a href="__SERVER_BASE_URL__">__SERVER_BASE_URL__</a> (CAS __CAS_VERSION__)</a></address></body></html>'
 138                  :'</body></html>'
 139              :$this->_output_footer
 140          );
 141      }

 194      /**
 195       * This method is used to set the language used by phpCAS.
 196       *
 197       * @param string $lang representing the language.
 198       *
 199       * @return void
 200       */
 201      public function setLang($lang)
 202      {
 203          // Argument Validation
 204          if (gettype($lang) != 'string')
 205              throw new CAS_TypeMismatchException($lang, '$lang', 'string');
 206  
 207          phpCAS::traceBegin();
 208          $obj = new $lang();
 209          if (!($obj instanceof CAS_Languages_LanguageInterface)) {
 210              throw new CAS_InvalidArgumentException(
 211                  '$className must implement the CAS_Languages_LanguageInterface'
 212              );
 213          }
 214          $this->_lang = $lang;
 215          phpCAS::traceEnd();
 216      }

 237      /**
 238       * a record to store information about the CAS server.
 239       * - $_server['version']: the version of the CAS server
 240       * - $_server['hostname']: the hostname of the CAS server
 241       * - $_server['port']: the port the CAS server is running on
 242       * - $_server['uri']: the base URI the CAS server is responding on
 243       * - $_server['base_url']: the base URL of the CAS server
 244       * - $_server['login_url']: the login URL of the CAS server
 245       * - $_server['service_validate_url']: the service validating URL of the
 246       *   CAS server
 247       * - $_server['proxy_url']: the proxy URL of the CAS server
 248       * - $_server['proxy_validate_url']: the proxy validating URL of the CAS server
 249       * - $_server['logout_url']: the logout URL of the CAS server
 250       *
 251       * $_server['version'], $_server['hostname'], $_server['port'] and
 252       * $_server['uri'] are written by CAS_Client::CAS_Client(), read by
 253       * CAS_Client::getServerVersion(), CAS_Client::_getServerHostname(),
 254       * CAS_Client::_getServerPort() and CAS_Client::_getServerURI().
 255       *
 256       * The other fields are written and read by CAS_Client::_getServerBaseURL(),
 257       * CAS_Client::getServerLoginURL(), CAS_Client::getServerServiceValidateURL(),
 258       * CAS_Client::getServerProxyValidateURL() and CAS_Client::getServerLogoutURL().
 259       *
 260       * @hideinitializer
 261       */

 263          'version' => -1,
 264          'hostname' => 'none',
 265          'port' => -1,
 266          'uri' => 'none');

 308      /**
 309       * This method is used to retrieve the base URL of the CAS server.
 310       *
 311       * @return string a URL.
 312       */
 313      private function _getServerBaseURL()
 314      {
 315          // the URL is build only when needed
 316          if ( empty($this->_server['base_url']) ) {
 317              $this->_server['base_url'] = 'https://' . $this->_getServerHostname();
 318              if ($this->_getServerPort()!=443) {
 319                  $this->_server['base_url'] .= ':'
 320                  .$this->_getServerPort();
 321              }
 322              $this->_server['base_url'] .= $this->_getServerURI();
 323          }
 324          return $this->_server['base_url'];
 325      }
 326  
 327      /**
 328       * This method is used to retrieve the login URL of the CAS server.
 329       *
 330       * @param bool $gateway true to check authentication, false to force it
 331       * @param bool $renew   true to force the authentication with the CAS server
 332       *
 333       * @return a URL.
 334       * @note It is recommended that CAS implementations ignore the "gateway"
 335       * parameter if "renew" is set
 336       */
 337      public function getServerLoginURL($gateway=false,$renew=false)
 338      {
 339          phpCAS::traceBegin();
 340          // the URL is build only when needed
 341          if ( empty($this->_server['login_url']) ) {
 342              $this->_server['login_url'] = $this->_buildQueryUrl($this->_getServerBaseURL().'login','service='.urlencode($this->getURL()));
 343          }
 344          $url = $this->_server['login_url'];
 345          if ($renew) {
 346              // It is recommended that when the "renew" parameter is set, its
 347              // value be "true"
 348              $url = $this->_buildQueryUrl($url, 'renew=true');
 349          } elseif ($gateway) {
 350              // It is recommended that when the "gateway" parameter is set, its
 351              // value be "true"
 352              $url = $this->_buildQueryUrl($url, 'gateway=true');
 353          }
 354          phpCAS::traceEnd($url);
 355          return $url;
 356      }

 426      /**
 427       * This method is used to retrieve the service validating URL of the CAS server.
 428       *
 429       * @return string serviceValidate URL.
 430       */
 431      public function getServerServiceValidateURL()
 432      {
 433          phpCAS::traceBegin();
 434          // the URL is build only when needed
 435          if ( empty($this->_server['service_validate_url']) ) {
 436              switch ($this->getServerVersion()) {
 437              case CAS_VERSION_1_0:
 438                  $this->_server['service_validate_url'] = $this->_getServerBaseURL()
 439                  .'validate';
 440                  break;
 441              case CAS_VERSION_2_0:
 442                  $this->_server['service_validate_url'] = $this->_getServerBaseURL()
 443                  .'serviceValidate';
 444                  break;
 445              case CAS_VERSION_3_0:
 446                  $this->_server['service_validate_url'] = $this->_getServerBaseURL()
 447                  .'p3/serviceValidate';
 448                  break;
 449              }
 450          }
 451          $url = $this->_buildQueryUrl(
 452              $this->_server['service_validate_url'],
 453              'service='.urlencode($this->getURL())
 454          );
 455          phpCAS::traceEnd($url);
 456          return $url;
 457      }
 458      /**
 459       * This method is used to retrieve the SAML validating URL of the CAS server.
 460       *
 461       * @return string samlValidate URL.
 462       */
 463      public function getServerSamlValidateURL()
 464      {
 465          phpCAS::traceBegin();
 466          // the URL is build only when needed
 467          if ( empty($this->_server['saml_validate_url']) ) {
 468              switch ($this->getServerVersion()) {
 469              case SAML_VERSION_1_1:
 470                  $this->_server['saml_validate_url'] = $this->_getServerBaseURL().'samlValidate';
 471                  break;
 472              }
 473          }
 474  
 475          $url = $this->_buildQueryUrl(
 476              $this->_server['saml_validate_url'],
 477              'TARGET='.urlencode($this->getURL())
 478          );
 479          phpCAS::traceEnd($url);
 480          return $url;
 481      }

 653      /**
 654       * Set a callback function to be run when a user authenticates.
 655       *
 656       * The callback function will be passed a $logoutTicket as its first parameter,
 657       * followed by any $additionalArgs you pass. The $logoutTicket parameter is an
 658       * opaque string that can be used to map a session-id to the logout request
 659       * in order to support single-signout in applications that manage their own
 660       * sessions (rather than letting phpCAS start the session).
 661       *
 662       * phpCAS::forceAuthentication() will always exit and forward client unless
 663       * they are already authenticated. To perform an action at the moment the user
 664       * logs in (such as registering an account, performing logging, etc), register
 665       * a callback function here.
 666       *
 667       * @param string $function       callback function to call
 668       * @param array  $additionalArgs optional array of arguments
 669       *
 670       * @return void
 671       */
 672      public function setPostAuthenticateCallback ($function, array $additionalArgs = array())
 673      {
 674          $this->_postAuthenticateCallbackFunction = $function;
 675          $this->_postAuthenticateCallbackArgs = $additionalArgs;
 676      }

 694       * order to support single-signout in applications that manage their own sessions
 695       * (rather than letting phpCAS start and destroy the session).

 697       * @param string $function       callback function to call

 726      /**
 727       * Mark the caller of authentication. This will help client integraters determine
 728       * problems with their code flow if they call a function such as getUser() before
 729       * authentication has occurred.
 730       *
 731       * @param bool $auth True if authentication was successful, false otherwise.
 732       *
 733       * @return null
 734       */
 735      public function markAuthenticationCall ($auth)
 736      {
 737          // store where the authentication has been checked and the result
 738          $dbg = debug_backtrace();
 739          $this->_authentication_caller = array (
 740              'file' => $dbg[1]['file'],
 741              'line' => $dbg[1]['line'],
 742              'method' => $dbg[1]['class'] . '::' . $dbg[1]['function'],
 743              'result' => (boolean)$auth
 744          );
 745      }
 746      private $_authentication_caller;
 747  
 748      /**
 749       * Answer true if authentication has been checked.
 750       *
 751       * @return bool
 752       */
 753      public function wasAuthenticationCalled ()
 754      {
 755          return !empty($this->_authentication_caller);
 756      }
 757  
 758      /**
 759       * Ensure that authentication was checked. Terminate with exception if no
 760       * authentication was performed
 761       *
 762       * @throws CAS_OutOfSequenceBeforeAuthenticationCallException
 763       *
 764       * @return void
 765       */
 766      private function _ensureAuthenticationCalled()
 767      {
 768          if (!$this->wasAuthenticationCalled()) {
 769              throw new CAS_OutOfSequenceBeforeAuthenticationCallException();
 770          }
 771      }
 772  
 773      /**
 774       * Answer the result of the authentication call.
 775       *
 776       * Throws a CAS_OutOfSequenceException if wasAuthenticationCalled() is false
 777       * and markAuthenticationCall() didn't happen.
 778       *
 779       * @return bool
 780       */
 781      public function wasAuthenticationCallSuccessful ()
 782      {
 783          $this->_ensureAuthenticationCalled();
 784          return $this->_authentication_caller['result'];
 785      }
 786  
 787  
 788      /**
 789       * Ensure that authentication was checked. Terminate with exception if no
 790       * authentication was performed
 791       *
 792       * @throws CAS_OutOfSequenceBeforeAuthenticationCallException
 793       *
 794       * @return void
 795       */
 796      public function ensureAuthenticationCallSuccessful()
 797      {
 798          $this->_ensureAuthenticationCalled();
 799          if (!$this->_authentication_caller['result']) {
 800              throw new CAS_OutOfSequenceException(
 801                  'authentication was checked (by '
 802                  . $this->getAuthenticationCallerMethod()
 803                  . '() at ' . $this->getAuthenticationCallerFile()
 804                  . ':' . $this->getAuthenticationCallerLine()
 805                  . ') but the method returned false'
 806              );
 807          }
 808      }
 809  
 810      /**
 811       * Answer information about the authentication caller.
 812       *
 813       * Throws a CAS_OutOfSequenceException if wasAuthenticationCalled() is false
 814       * and markAuthenticationCall() didn't happen.
 815       *
 816       * @return array Keys are 'file', 'line', and 'method'
 817       */
 818      public function getAuthenticationCallerFile ()
 819      {
 820          $this->_ensureAuthenticationCalled();
 821          return $this->_authentication_caller['file'];
 822      }
 823  
 824      /**
 825       * Answer information about the authentication caller.
 826       *
 827       * Throws a CAS_OutOfSequenceException if wasAuthenticationCalled() is false
 828       * and markAuthenticationCall() didn't happen.
 829       *
 830       * @return array Keys are 'file', 'line', and 'method'
 831       */
 832      public function getAuthenticationCallerLine ()
 833      {
 834          $this->_ensureAuthenticationCalled();
 835          return $this->_authentication_caller['line'];
 836      }
 837  
 838      /**
 839       * Answer information about the authentication caller.
 840       *
 841       * Throws a CAS_OutOfSequenceException if wasAuthenticationCalled() is false
 842       * and markAuthenticationCall() didn't happen.
 843       *
 844       * @return array Keys are 'file', 'line', and 'method'
 845       */
 846      public function getAuthenticationCallerMethod ()
 847      {
 848          $this->_ensureAuthenticationCalled();
 849          return $this->_authentication_caller['method'];
 850      }

 862      /**
 863       * CAS_Client constructor.
 864       *
 865       * @param string $server_version  the version of the CAS server
 866       * @param bool   $proxy           true if the CAS client is a CAS proxy
 867       * @param string $server_hostname the hostname of the CAS server
 868       * @param int    $server_port     the port the CAS server is running on
 869       * @param string $server_uri      the URI the CAS server is responding on
 870       * @param bool   $changeSessionID Allow phpCAS to change the session_id
 871       *                                (Single Sign Out/handleLogoutRequests
 872       *                                is based on that change)
 873       *
 874       * @return a newly created CAS_Client object
 875       */
 876      public function __construct(
 877          $server_version,
 878          $proxy,
 879          $server_hostname,
 880          $server_port,
 881          $server_uri,
 882          $changeSessionID = true
 883      ) {
 884          // Argument validation
 885          if (gettype($server_version) != 'string')
 886              throw new CAS_TypeMismatchException($server_version, '$server_version', 'string');
 887          if (gettype($proxy) != 'boolean')
 888              throw new CAS_TypeMismatchException($proxy, '$proxy', 'boolean');
 889          if (gettype($server_hostname) != 'string')
 890              throw new CAS_TypeMismatchException($server_hostname, '$server_hostname', 'string');
 891          if (gettype($server_port) != 'integer')
 892              throw new CAS_TypeMismatchException($server_port, '$server_port', 'integer');
 893          if (gettype($server_uri) != 'string')
 894              throw new CAS_TypeMismatchException($server_uri, '$server_uri', 'string');
 895          if (gettype($changeSessionID) != 'boolean')
 896              throw new CAS_TypeMismatchException($changeSessionID, '$changeSessionID', 'boolean');
 897  
 898          phpCAS::traceBegin();
 899          // true : allow to change the session_id(), false session_id won't be
 900          // change and logout won't be handle because of that
 901          $this->_setChangeSessionID($changeSessionID);
 902  
 903          // skip Session Handling for logout requests and if don't want it'
 904          if (session_id()=="" && !$this->_isLogoutRequest()) {
 905              session_start();
 906              phpCAS :: trace("Starting a new session " . session_id());
 907          }
 908  
 909          // are we in proxy mode ?
 910          $this->_proxy = $proxy;
 911  
 912          // Make cookie handling available.
 913          if ($this->isProxy()) {
 914              if (!isset($_SESSION['phpCAS'])) {
 915                  $_SESSION['phpCAS'] = array();
 916              }
 917              if (!isset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['service_cookies'])) {
 918                  $_SESSION['phpCAS']['service_cookies'] = array();
 919              }
 920              $this->_serviceCookieJar = new CAS_CookieJar(
 921                  $_SESSION['phpCAS']['service_cookies']
 922              );
 923          }
 924  
 925          //check version
 926          switch ($server_version) {
 927          case CAS_VERSION_1_0:
 928              if ( $this->isProxy() ) {
 929                  phpCAS::error(
 930                      'CAS proxies are not supported in CAS '.$server_version
 931                  );
 932              }
 933              break;
 934          case CAS_VERSION_2_0:
 935          case CAS_VERSION_3_0:
 936              break;
 937          case SAML_VERSION_1_1:
 938              break;
 939          default:
 940              phpCAS::error(
 941                  'this version of CAS (`'.$server_version
 942                  .'\') is not supported by phpCAS '.phpCAS::getVersion()
 943              );
 944          }
 945          $this->_server['version'] = $server_version;
 946  
 947          // check hostname
 948          if ( empty($server_hostname)
 949              || !preg_match('/[\.\d\-abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz]*/', $server_hostname)
 950          ) {
 951              phpCAS::error('bad CAS server hostname (`'.$server_hostname.'\')');
 952          }
 953          $this->_server['hostname'] = $server_hostname;
 954  
 955          // check port
 956          if ( $server_port == 0
 957              || !is_int($server_port)
 958          ) {
 959              phpCAS::error('bad CAS server port (`'.$server_hostname.'\')');
 960          }
 961          $this->_server['port'] = $server_port;
 962  
 963          // check URI
 964          if ( !preg_match('/[\.\d\-_abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz\/]*/', $server_uri) ) {
 965              phpCAS::error('bad CAS server URI (`'.$server_uri.'\')');
 966          }
 967          // add leading and trailing `/' and remove doubles
 968          if(strstr($server_uri, '?') === false) $server_uri .= '/';
 969          $server_uri = preg_replace('/\/\//', '/', '/'.$server_uri);
 970          $this->_server['uri'] = $server_uri;
 971  
 972          // set to callback mode if PgtIou and PgtId CGI GET parameters are provided
 973          if ( $this->isProxy() ) {
 974              $this->_setCallbackMode(!empty($_GET['pgtIou'])&&!empty($_GET['pgtId']));
 975          }
 976  
 977          if ( $this->_isCallbackMode() ) {
 978              //callback mode: check that phpCAS is secured
 979              if ( !$this->_isHttps() ) {
 980                  phpCAS::error(
 981                      'CAS proxies must be secured to use phpCAS; PGT\'s will not be received from the CAS server'
 982                  );
 983              }
 984          } else {
 985              //normal mode: get ticket and remove it from CGI parameters for
 986              // developers
 987              $ticket = (isset($_GET['ticket']) ? $_GET['ticket'] : null);
 988              if (preg_match('/^[SP]T-/', $ticket) ) {
 989                  phpCAS::trace('Ticket \''.$ticket.'\' found');
 990                  $this->setTicket($ticket);
 991                  unset($_GET['ticket']);
 992              } else if ( !empty($ticket) ) {
 993                  //ill-formed ticket, halt
 994                  phpCAS::error(
 995                      'ill-formed ticket found in the URL (ticket=`'
 996                      .htmlentities($ticket).'\')'
 997                  );
 998              }
 999  
1000          }
1001          phpCAS::traceEnd();
1002      }

1213      /**
1214       * This method is called to renew the authentication of the user
1215       * If the user is authenticated, renew the connection
1216       * If not, redirect to CAS
1217       *
1218       * @return  true when the user is authenticated; otherwise halt.
1219       */
1220      public function renewAuthentication()
1221      {
1222          phpCAS::traceBegin();
1223          // Either way, the user is authenticated by CAS
1224          if (isset( $_SESSION['phpCAS']['auth_checked'])) {
1225              unset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['auth_checked']);
1226          }
1227          if ( $this->isAuthenticated(true) ) {
1228              phpCAS::trace('user already authenticated');
1229              $res = true;
1230          } else {
1231              $this->redirectToCas(false, true);
1232              // never reached

1233              $res = false;
1234          }
1235          phpCAS::traceEnd();
1236          return $res;
1237      }
1238  
1239      /**
1240       * This method is called to be sure that the user is authenticated. When not
1241       * authenticated, halt by redirecting to the CAS server; otherwise return true.
1242       *
1243       * @return true when the user is authenticated; otherwise halt.
1244       */
1245      public function forceAuthentication()
1246      {
1247          phpCAS::traceBegin();
1248  
1249          if ( $this->isAuthenticated() ) {
1250              // the user is authenticated, nothing to be done.
1251              phpCAS::trace('no need to authenticate');
1252              $res = true;
1253          } else {
1254              // the user is not authenticated, redirect to the CAS server
1255              if (isset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['auth_checked'])) {
1256                  unset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['auth_checked']);
1257              }
1258              $this->redirectToCas(false/* no gateway */);
1259              // never reached
1260              $res = false;
1261          }
1262          phpCAS::traceEnd($res);
1263          return $res;
1264      }
1265  
1266      /**
1267       * An integer that gives the number of times authentication will be cached
1268       * before rechecked.
1269       *
1270       * @hideinitializer
1271       */
1272      private $_cache_times_for_auth_recheck = 0;
1273  
1274      /**
1275       * Set the number of times authentication will be cached before rechecked.
1276       *
1277       * @param int $n number of times to wait for a recheck
1278       *
1279       * @return void
1280       */
1281      public function setCacheTimesForAuthRecheck($n)
1282      {
1283          if (gettype($n) != 'integer')
1284              throw new CAS_TypeMismatchException($n, '$n', 'string');
1285  
1286          $this->_cache_times_for_auth_recheck = $n;
1287      }
1288  
1289      /**
1290       * This method is called to check whether the user is authenticated or not.
1291       *
1292       * @return true when the user is authenticated, false when a previous
1293       * gateway login failed or  the function will not return if the user is
1294       * redirected to the cas server for a gateway login attempt
1295       */
1296      public function checkAuthentication()
1297      {
1298          phpCAS::traceBegin();
1299          $res = false;
1300          if ( $this->isAuthenticated() ) {
1301              phpCAS::trace('user is authenticated');
1302              /* The 'auth_checked' variable is removed just in case it's set. */
1303              unset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['auth_checked']);
1304              $res = true;
1305          } else if (isset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['auth_checked'])) {
1306              // the previous request has redirected the client to the CAS server
1307              // with gateway=true
1308              unset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['auth_checked']);
1309              $res = false;
1310          } else {
1311              // avoid a check against CAS on every request
1312              if (!isset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['unauth_count'])) {
1313                  $_SESSION['phpCAS']['unauth_count'] = -2; // uninitialized
1314              }
1315  
1316              if (($_SESSION['phpCAS']['unauth_count'] != -2
1317                  && $this->_cache_times_for_auth_recheck == -1)
1318                  || ($_SESSION['phpCAS']['unauth_count'] >= 0
1319                  && $_SESSION['phpCAS']['unauth_count'] < $this->_cache_times_for_auth_recheck)
1320              ) {
1321                  $res = false;
1322  
1323                  if ($this->_cache_times_for_auth_recheck != -1) {
1324                      $_SESSION['phpCAS']['unauth_count']++;
1325                      phpCAS::trace(
1326                          'user is not authenticated (cached for '
1327                          .$_SESSION['phpCAS']['unauth_count'].' times of '
1328                          .$this->_cache_times_for_auth_recheck.')'
1329                      );
1330                  } else {
1331                      phpCAS::trace(
1332                          'user is not authenticated (cached for until login pressed)'
1333                      );
1334                  }
1335              } else {
1336                  $_SESSION['phpCAS']['unauth_count'] = 0;
1337                  $_SESSION['phpCAS']['auth_checked'] = true;
1338                  phpCAS::trace('user is not authenticated (cache reset)');
1339                  $this->redirectToCas(true/* gateway */);
1340                  // never reached
1341                  $res = false;
1342              }
1343          }
1344          phpCAS::traceEnd($res);
1345          return $res;
1346      }
1347  
1348      /**
1349       * This method is called to check if the user is authenticated (previously or by
1350       * tickets given in the URL).
1351       *
1352       * @param bool $renew true to force the authentication with the CAS server
1353       *
1354       * @return true when the user is authenticated. Also may redirect to the
1355       * same URL without the ticket.
1356       */
1357      public function isAuthenticated($renew=false)
1358      {
1359          phpCAS::traceBegin();
1360          $res = false;
1361          $validate_url = '';
1362          if ( $this->_wasPreviouslyAuthenticated() ) {
1363              if ($this->hasTicket()) {
1364                  // User has a additional ticket but was already authenticated
1365                  phpCAS::trace(
1366                      'ticket was present and will be discarded, use renewAuthenticate()'
1367                  );
1368                  if ($this->_clearTicketsFromUrl) {
1369                      phpCAS::trace("Prepare redirect to : ".$this->getURL());
1370                      session_write_close();
1371                      header('Location: '.$this->getURL());
1372                      flush();
1373                      phpCAS::traceExit();
1374                      throw new CAS_GracefullTerminationException();
1375                  } else {
1376                      phpCAS::trace(
1377                          'Already authenticated, but skipping ticket clearing since setNoClearTicketsFromUrl() was used.'
1378                      );
1379                      $res = true;
1380                  }
1381              } else {
1382                  // the user has already (previously during the session) been
1383                  // authenticated, nothing to be done.
1384                  phpCAS::trace(
1385                      'user was already authenticated, no need to look for tickets'
1386                  );
1387                  $res = true;
1388              }
1389  
1390              // Mark the auth-check as complete to allow post-authentication
1391              // callbacks to make use of phpCAS::getUser() and similar methods
1392              $this->markAuthenticationCall($res);
1393          } else {
1394              if ($this->hasTicket()) {
1395                  switch ($this->getServerVersion()) {
1396                  case CAS_VERSION_1_0:
1397                      // if a Service Ticket was given, validate it
1398                      phpCAS::trace(
1399                          'CAS 1.0 ticket `'.$this->getTicket().'\' is present'
1400                      );
1401                      $this->validateCAS10(
1402                          $validate_url, $text_response, $tree_response, $renew
1403                      ); // if it fails, it halts
1404                      phpCAS::trace(
1405                          'CAS 1.0 ticket `'.$this->getTicket().'\' was validated'
1406                      );
1407                      $_SESSION['phpCAS']['user'] = $this->_getUser();
1408                      $res = true;
1409                      $logoutTicket = $this->getTicket();
1410                      break;
1411                  case CAS_VERSION_2_0:
1412                  case CAS_VERSION_3_0:
1413                      // if a Proxy Ticket was given, validate it
1414                      phpCAS::trace(
1415                          'CAS '.$this->getServerVersion().' ticket `'.$this->getTicket().'\' is present'
1416                      );
1417                      $this->validateCAS20(
1418                          $validate_url, $text_response, $tree_response, $renew
1419                      ); // note: if it fails, it halts
1420                      phpCAS::trace(
1421                          'CAS '.$this->getServerVersion().' ticket `'.$this->getTicket().'\' was validated'
1422                      );
1423                      if ( $this->isProxy() ) {
1424                          $this->_validatePGT(
1425                              $validate_url, $text_response, $tree_response
1426                          ); // idem
1427                          phpCAS::trace('PGT `'.$this->_getPGT().'\' was validated');
1428                          $_SESSION['phpCAS']['pgt'] = $this->_getPGT();
1429                      }
1430                      $_SESSION['phpCAS']['user'] = $this->_getUser();
1431                      if (!empty($this->_attributes)) {
1432                          $_SESSION['phpCAS']['attributes'] = $this->_attributes;
1433                      }
1434                      $proxies = $this->getProxies();
1435                      if (!empty($proxies)) {
1436                          $_SESSION['phpCAS']['proxies'] = $this->getProxies();
1437                      }
1438                      $res = true;
1439                      $logoutTicket = $this->getTicket();
1440                      break;
1441                  case SAML_VERSION_1_1:
1442                      // if we have a SAML ticket, validate it.
1443                      phpCAS::trace(
1444                          'SAML 1.1 ticket `'.$this->getTicket().'\' is present'
1445                      );
1446                      $this->validateSA(
1447                          $validate_url, $text_response, $tree_response, $renew
1448                      ); // if it fails, it halts
1449                      phpCAS::trace(
1450                          'SAML 1.1 ticket `'.$this->getTicket().'\' was validated'
1451                      );
1452                      $_SESSION['phpCAS']['user'] = $this->_getUser();
1453                      $_SESSION['phpCAS']['attributes'] = $this->_attributes;
1454                      $res = true;
1455                      $logoutTicket = $this->getTicket();
1456                      break;
1457                  default:
1458                      phpCAS::trace('Protocoll error');
1459                      break;
1460                  }
1461              } else {
1462                  // no ticket given, not authenticated
1463                  phpCAS::trace('no ticket found');
1464              }
1465  
1466              // Mark the auth-check as complete to allow post-authentication
1467              // callbacks to make use of phpCAS::getUser() and similar methods
1468              $this->markAuthenticationCall($res);
1469  
1470              if ($res) {
1471                  // call the post-authenticate callback if registered.
1472                  if ($this->_postAuthenticateCallbackFunction) {
1473                      $args = $this->_postAuthenticateCallbackArgs;
1474                      array_unshift($args, $logoutTicket);
1475                      call_user_func_array(
1476                          $this->_postAuthenticateCallbackFunction, $args
1477                      );
1478                  }
1479  
1480                  // if called with a ticket parameter, we need to redirect to the
1481                  // app without the ticket so that CAS-ification is transparent
1482                  // to the browser (for later POSTS) most of the checks and
1483                  // errors should have been made now, so we're safe for redirect
1484                  // without masking error messages. remove the ticket as a
1485                  // security precaution to prevent a ticket in the HTTP_REFERRER
1486                  if ($this->_clearTicketsFromUrl) {
1487                      phpCAS::trace("Prepare redirect to : ".$this->getURL());
1488                      session_write_close();
1489                      header('Location: '.$this->getURL());
1490                      flush();
1491                      phpCAS::traceExit();
1492                      throw new CAS_GracefullTerminationException();
1493                  }
1494              }
1495          }
1496          phpCAS::traceEnd($res);
1497          return $res;
1498      }

1500      /**
1501       * This method tells if the current session is authenticated.
1502       *
1503       * @return true if authenticated based soley on $_SESSION variable
1504       */
1505      public function isSessionAuthenticated ()
1506      {
1507          return !empty($_SESSION['phpCAS']['user']);
1508      }

1510      /**
1511       * This method tells if the user has already been (previously) authenticated
1512       * by looking into the session variables.
1513       *
1514       * @note This function switches to callback mode when needed.
1515       *
1516       * @return true when the user has already been authenticated; false otherwise.
1517       */
1518      private function _wasPreviouslyAuthenticated()
1519      {
1520          phpCAS::traceBegin();
1521  
1522          if ( $this->_isCallbackMode() ) {
1523              // Rebroadcast the pgtIou and pgtId to all nodes
1524              if ($this->_rebroadcast&&!isset($_POST['rebroadcast'])) {
1525                  $this->_rebroadcast(self::PGTIOU);
1526              }
1527              $this->_callback();
1528          }
1529  
1530          $auth = false;
1531  
1532          if ( $this->isProxy() ) {
1533              // CAS proxy: username and PGT must be present
1534              if ( $this->isSessionAuthenticated()
1535                  && !empty($_SESSION['phpCAS']['pgt'])
1536              ) {
1537                  // authentication already done
1538                  $this->_setUser($_SESSION['phpCAS']['user']);
1539                  if (isset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['attributes'])) {
1540                      $this->setAttributes($_SESSION['phpCAS']['attributes']);
1541                  }
1542                  $this->_setPGT($_SESSION['phpCAS']['pgt']);
1543                  phpCAS::trace(
1544                      'user = `'.$_SESSION['phpCAS']['user'].'\', PGT = `'
1545                      .$_SESSION['phpCAS']['pgt'].'\''
1546                  );
1547  
1548                  // Include the list of proxies
1549                  if (isset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['proxies'])) {
1550                      $this->_setProxies($_SESSION['phpCAS']['proxies']);
1551                      phpCAS::trace(
1552                          'proxies = "'
1553                          .implode('", "', $_SESSION['phpCAS']['proxies']).'"'
1554                      );
1555                  }
1556  
1557                  $auth = true;
1558              } elseif ( $this->isSessionAuthenticated()
1559                  && empty($_SESSION['phpCAS']['pgt'])
1560              ) {
1561                  // these two variables should be empty or not empty at the same time
1562                  phpCAS::trace(
1563                      'username found (`'.$_SESSION['phpCAS']['user']
1564                      .'\') but PGT is empty'
1565                  );
1566                  // unset all tickets to enforce authentication
1567                  unset($_SESSION['phpCAS']);
1568                  $this->setTicket('');
1569              } elseif ( !$this->isSessionAuthenticated()
1570                  && !empty($_SESSION['phpCAS']['pgt'])
1571              ) {
1572                  // these two variables should be empty or not empty at the same time
1573                  phpCAS::trace(
1574                      'PGT found (`'.$_SESSION['phpCAS']['pgt']
1575                      .'\') but username is empty'
1576                  );
1577                  // unset all tickets to enforce authentication
1578                  unset($_SESSION['phpCAS']);
1579                  $this->setTicket('');
1580              } else {
1581                  phpCAS::trace('neither user nor PGT found');
1582              }
1583          } else {
1584              // `simple' CAS client (not a proxy): username must be present
1585              if ( $this->isSessionAuthenticated() ) {
1586                  // authentication already done
1587                  $this->_setUser($_SESSION['phpCAS']['user']);
1588                  if (isset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['attributes'])) {
1589                      $this->setAttributes($_SESSION['phpCAS']['attributes']);
1590                  }
1591                  phpCAS::trace('user = `'.$_SESSION['phpCAS']['user'].'\'');
1592  
1593                  // Include the list of proxies
1594                  if (isset($_SESSION['phpCAS']['proxies'])) {
1595                      $this->_setProxies($_SESSION['phpCAS']['proxies']);
1596                      phpCAS::trace(
1597                          'proxies = "'
1598                          .implode('", "', $_SESSION['phpCAS']['proxies']).'"'
1599                      );
1600                  }
1601  
1602                  $auth = true;
1603              } else {
1604                  phpCAS::trace('no user found');
1605              }
1606          }
1607  
1608          phpCAS::traceEnd($auth);
1609          return $auth;
1610      }

1613       * This method is used to redirect the client to the CAS server.
1614       * It is used by CAS_Client::forceAuthentication() and
1615       * CAS_Client::checkAuthentication().
1616       *
1617       * @param bool $gateway true to check authentication, false to force it
1618       * @param bool $renew   true to force the authentication with the CAS server
1619       *
1620       * @return void
1621       */
1622      public function redirectToCas($gateway=false,$renew=false)

1624          phpCAS::traceBegin();
1625          $cas_url = $this->getServerLoginURL($gateway, $renew);
1626          session_write_close();

1628              @header('Location: '.$cas_url);
1629          } else {
1630              header('Location: '.$cas_url);
1631          }
1632          phpCAS::trace("Redirect to : ".$cas_url);
1633          $lang = $this->getLangObj();
1634          $this->printHTMLHeader($lang->getAuthenticationWanted());
1635          printf('<p>'. $lang->getShouldHaveBeenRedirected(). '</p>', $cas_url);
1636          $this->printHTMLFooter();
1637          phpCAS::traceExit();
1638          throw new CAS_GracefullTerminationException();

1643       * This method is used to logout from CAS.
1644       *
1645       * @param array $params an array that contains the optional url and service
1646       * parameters that will be passed to the CAS server
1647       *
1648       * @return void
1649       */
1650      public function logout($params)
1651      {
1652          phpCAS::traceBegin();
1653          $cas_url = $this->getServerLogoutURL();
1654          $paramSeparator = '?';
1655          if (isset($params['url'])) {
1656              $cas_url = $cas_url . $paramSeparator . "url="
1657                  . urlencode($params['url']);
1658              $paramSeparator = '&';
1659          }
1660          if (isset($params['service'])) {
1661              $cas_url = $cas_url . $paramSeparator . "service="
1662                  . urlencode($params['service']);
1663          }
1664          header('Location: '.$cas_url);
1665          phpCAS::trace("Prepare redirect to : ".$cas_url);
1666  
1667          session_unset();
1668          session_destroy();
1669          $lang = $this->getLangObj();
1670          $this->printHTMLHeader($lang->getLogout());
1671          printf('<p>'.$lang->getShouldHaveBeenRedirected(). '</p>', $cas_url);
1672          $this->printHTMLFooter();
1673          phpCAS::traceExit();
1674          throw new CAS_GracefullTerminationException();
1675      }

1678       * Check of the current request is a logout request

1684          return !empty($_POST['logoutRequest']);

1687      /**
1688       * This method handles logout requests.
1689       *
1690       * @param bool $check_client    true to check the client bofore handling
1691       * the request, false not to perform any access control. True by default.
1692       * @param bool $allowed_clients an array of host names allowed to send
1693       * logout requests.
1694       *
1695       * @return void
1696       */
1697      public function handleLogoutRequests($check_client=true, $allowed_clients=false)
1698      {
1699          phpCAS::traceBegin();
1700          if (!$this->_isLogoutRequest()) {
1701              phpCAS::trace("Not a logout request");
1702              phpCAS::traceEnd();
1703              return;
1704          }
1705          if (!$this->getChangeSessionID()
1706              && is_null($this->_signoutCallbackFunction)
1707          ) {
1708              phpCAS::trace(
1709                  "phpCAS can't handle logout requests if it is not allowed to change session_id."
1710              );
1711          }
1712          phpCAS::trace("Logout requested");
1713          $decoded_logout_rq = urldecode($_POST['logoutRequest']);
1714          phpCAS::trace("SAML REQUEST: ".$decoded_logout_rq);
1715          $allowed = false;
1716          if ($check_client) {
1717              if (!$allowed_clients) {
1718                  $allowed_clients = array( $this->_getServerHostname() );
1719              }
1720              $client_ip = $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'];
1721              $client = gethostbyaddr($client_ip);
1722              phpCAS::trace("Client: ".$client."/".$client_ip);
1723              foreach ($allowed_clients as $allowed_client) {
1724                  if (($client == $allowed_client)
1725                      || ($client_ip == $allowed_client)
1726                  ) {
1727                      phpCAS::trace(
1728                          "Allowed client '".$allowed_client
1729                          ."' matches, logout request is allowed"
1730                      );
1731                      $allowed = true;
1732                      break;
1733                  } else {
1734                      phpCAS::trace(
1735                          "Allowed client '".$allowed_client."' does not match"
1736                      );
1737                  }
1738              }
1739          } else {
1740              phpCAS::trace("No access control set");
1741              $allowed = true;
1742          }
1743          // If Logout command is permitted proceed with the logout
1744          if ($allowed) {
1745              phpCAS::trace("Logout command allowed");
1746              // Rebroadcast the logout request
1747              if ($this->_rebroadcast && !isset($_POST['rebroadcast'])) {
1748                  $this->_rebroadcast(self::LOGOUT);
1749              }
1750              // Extract the ticket from the SAML Request
1751              preg_match(
1752                  "|<samlp:SessionIndex>(.*)</samlp:SessionIndex>|",
1753                  $decoded_logout_rq, $tick, PREG_OFFSET_CAPTURE, 3
1754              );
1755              $wrappedSamlSessionIndex = preg_replace(
1756                  '|<samlp:SessionIndex>|', '', $tick[0][0]
1757              );
1758              $ticket2logout = preg_replace(
1759                  '|</samlp:SessionIndex>|', '', $wrappedSamlSessionIndex
1760              );
1761              phpCAS::trace("Ticket to logout: ".$ticket2logout);
1762  
1763              // call the post-authenticate callback if registered.
1764              if ($this->_signoutCallbackFunction) {
1765                  $args = $this->_signoutCallbackArgs;
1766                  array_unshift($args, $ticket2logout);
1767                  call_user_func_array($this->_signoutCallbackFunction, $args);
1768              }
1769  
1770              // If phpCAS is managing the session_id, destroy session thanks to
1771              // session_id.
1772              if ($this->getChangeSessionID()) {
1773                  $session_id = preg_replace('/[^a-zA-Z0-9\-]/', '', $ticket2logout);
1774                  phpCAS::trace("Session id: ".$session_id);
1775  
1776                  // destroy a possible application session created before phpcas
1777                  if (session_id() !== "") {
1778                      session_unset();
1779                      session_destroy();
1780                  }
1781                  // fix session ID
1782                  session_id($session_id);
1783                  $_COOKIE[session_name()]=$session_id;
1784                  $_GET[session_name()]=$session_id;
1785  
1786                  // Overwrite session
1787                  session_start();
1788                  session_unset();
1789                  session_destroy();
1790                  phpCAS::trace("Session ". $session_id . " destroyed");
1791              }
1792          } else {
1793              phpCAS::error("Unauthorized logout request from client '".$client."'");
1794              phpCAS::trace("Unauthorized logout request from client '".$client."'");
1795          }
1796          flush();
1797          phpCAS::traceExit();
1798          throw new CAS_GracefullTerminationException();
1799  
1800      }

1928      /**
1929       * This method is used to validate a CAS 1,0 ticket; halt on failure, and
1930       * sets $validate_url, $text_reponse and $tree_response on success.
1931       *
1932       * @param string &$validate_url  reference to the the URL of the request to
1933       * the CAS server.
1934       * @param string &$text_response reference to the response of the CAS
1935       * server, as is (XML text).
1936       * @param string &$tree_response reference to the response of the CAS
1937       * server, as a DOM XML tree.
1938       * @param bool   $renew          true to force the authentication with the CAS server
1939       *
1940       * @return bool true when successfull and issue a CAS_AuthenticationException
1941       * and false on an error
1942       */
1943      public function validateCAS10(&$validate_url,&$text_response,&$tree_response,$renew=false)
1944      {
1945          phpCAS::traceBegin();
1946          $result = false;
1947          // build the URL to validate the ticket
1948          $validate_url = $this->getServerServiceValidateURL()
1949              .'&ticket='.urlencode($this->getTicket());
1950  
1951          if ( $renew ) {
1952              // pass the renew

1953              $validate_url .= '&renew=true';
1954          }
1955  
1956          // open and read the URL
1957          if ( !$this->_readURL($validate_url, $headers, $text_response, $err_msg) ) {
1958              phpCAS::trace(
1959                  'could not open URL \''.$validate_url.'\' to validate ('.$err_msg.')'
1960              );
1961              throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
1962                  $this, 'CAS 1.0 ticket not validated', $validate_url,
1963                  true/*$no_response*/
1964              );
1965              $result = false;
1966          }
1967  
1968          if (preg_match('/^no\n/', $text_response)) {
1969              phpCAS::trace('Ticket has not been validated');
1970              throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
1971                  $this, 'ST not validated', $validate_url, false/*$no_response*/,
1972                  false/*$bad_response*/, $text_response
1973              );
1974              $result = false;
1975          } else if (!preg_match('/^yes\n/', $text_response)) {
1976              phpCAS::trace('ill-formed response');
1977              throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
1978                  $this, 'Ticket not validated', $validate_url,
1979                  false/*$no_response*/, true/*$bad_response*/, $text_response
1980              );
1981              $result = false;
1982          }
1983          // ticket has been validated, extract the user name
1984          $arr = preg_split('/\n/', $text_response);
1985          $this->_setUser(trim($arr[1]));
1986          $result = true;
1987  
1988          if ($result) {
1989              $this->_renameSession($this->getTicket());
1990          }
1991          // at this step, ticket has been validated and $this->_user has been set,
1992          phpCAS::traceEnd(true);
1993          return true;
1994      }

2007      /**
2008       * This method is used to validate a SAML TICKET; halt on failure, and sets
2009       * $validate_url, $text_reponse and $tree_response on success. These
2010       * parameters are used later by CAS_Client::_validatePGT() for CAS proxies.
2011       *
2012       * @param string &$validate_url  reference to the the URL of the request to
2013       * the CAS server.
2014       * @param string &$text_response reference to the response of the CAS
2015       * server, as is (XML text).
2016       * @param string &$tree_response reference to the response of the CAS
2017       * server, as a DOM XML tree.
2018       * @param bool   $renew          true to force the authentication with the CAS server
2019       *
2020       * @return bool true when successfull and issue a CAS_AuthenticationException
2021       * and false on an error
2022       */
2023      public function validateSA(&$validate_url,&$text_response,&$tree_response,$renew=false)
2024      {
2025          phpCAS::traceBegin();
2026          $result = false;
2027          // build the URL to validate the ticket
2028          $validate_url = $this->getServerSamlValidateURL();
2029  
2030          if ( $renew ) {
2031              // pass the renew

2032              $validate_url .= '&renew=true';
2033          }
2034  
2035          // open and read the URL
2036          if ( !$this->_readURL($validate_url, $headers, $text_response, $err_msg) ) {
2037              phpCAS::trace(
2038                  'could not open URL \''.$validate_url.'\' to validate ('.$err_msg.')'
2039              );
2040              throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
2041                  $this, 'SA not validated', $validate_url, true/*$no_response*/
2042              );
2043          }
2044  
2045          phpCAS::trace('server version: '.$this->getServerVersion());
2046  
2047          // analyze the result depending on the version
2048          switch ($this->getServerVersion()) {
2049          case SAML_VERSION_1_1:
2050              // create new DOMDocument Object
2051              $dom = new DOMDocument();
2052              // Fix possible whitspace problems
2053              $dom->preserveWhiteSpace = false;
2054              // read the response of the CAS server into a DOM object
2055              if (!($dom->loadXML($text_response))) {
2056                  phpCAS::trace('dom->loadXML() failed');
2057                  throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
2058                      $this, 'SA not validated', $validate_url,
2059                      false/*$no_response*/, true/*$bad_response*/,
2060                      $text_response
2061                  );
2062                  $result = false;
2063              }
2064              // read the root node of the XML tree
2065              if (!($tree_response = $dom->documentElement)) {
2066                  phpCAS::trace('documentElement() failed');
2067                  throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
2068                      $this, 'SA not validated', $validate_url,
2069                      false/*$no_response*/, true/*$bad_response*/,
2070                      $text_response
2071                  );
2072                  $result = false;
2073              } else if ( $tree_response->localName != 'Envelope' ) {
2074                  // insure that tag name is 'Envelope'
2075                  phpCAS::trace(
2076                      'bad XML root node (should be `Envelope\' instead of `'
2077                      .$tree_response->localName.'\''
2078                  );
2079                  throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
2080                      $this, 'SA not validated', $validate_url,
2081                      false/*$no_response*/, true/*$bad_response*/,
2082                      $text_response
2083                  );
2084                  $result = false;
2085              } else if ($tree_response->getElementsByTagName("NameIdentifier")->length != 0) {
2086                  // check for the NameIdentifier tag in the SAML response
2087                  $success_elements = $tree_response->getElementsByTagName("NameIdentifier");
2088                  phpCAS::trace('NameIdentifier found');
2089                  $user = trim($success_elements->item(0)->nodeValue);
2090                  phpCAS::trace('user = `'.$user.'`');
2091                  $this->_setUser($user);
2092                  $this->_setSessionAttributes($text_response);
2093                  $result = true;
2094              } else {
2095                  phpCAS::trace('no <NameIdentifier> tag found in SAML payload');
2096                  throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
2097                      $this, 'SA not validated', $validate_url,
2098                      false/*$no_response*/, true/*$bad_response*/,
2099                      $text_response
2100                  );
2101                  $result = false;
2102              }
2103          }
2104          if ($result) {
2105              $this->_renameSession($this->getTicket());
2106          }
2107          // at this step, ST has been validated and $this->_user has been set,
2108          phpCAS::traceEnd($result);
2109          return $result;
2110      }
2111  
2112      /**
2113       * This method will parse the DOM and pull out the attributes from the SAML
2114       * payload and put them into an array, then put the array into the session.
2115       *
2116       * @param string $text_response the SAML payload.
2117       *
2118       * @return bool true when successfull and false if no attributes a found
2119       */
2120      private function _setSessionAttributes($text_response)
2121      {
2122          phpCAS::traceBegin();
2123  
2124          $result = false;
2125  
2126          $attr_array = array();
2127  
2128          // create new DOMDocument Object
2129          $dom = new DOMDocument();
2130          // Fix possible whitspace problems
2131          $dom->preserveWhiteSpace = false;
2132          if (($dom->loadXML($text_response))) {
2133              $xPath = new DOMXpath($dom);
2134              $xPath->registerNamespace('samlp', 'urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:1.0:protocol');
2135              $xPath->registerNamespace('saml', 'urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:1.0:assertion');
2136              $nodelist = $xPath->query("//saml:Attribute");
2137  
2138              if ($nodelist) {
2139                  foreach ($nodelist as $node) {
2140                      $xres = $xPath->query("saml:AttributeValue", $node);
2141                      $name = $node->getAttribute("AttributeName");
2142                      $value_array = array();
2143                      foreach ($xres as $node2) {
2144                          $value_array[] = $node2->nodeValue;
2145                      }
2146                      $attr_array[$name] = $value_array;
2147                  }
2148                  // UGent addition...
2149                  foreach ($attr_array as $attr_key => $attr_value) {
2150                      if (count($attr_value) > 1) {
2151                          $this->_attributes[$attr_key] = $attr_value;
2152                          phpCAS::trace("* " . $attr_key . "=" . print_r($attr_value, true));
2153                      } else {
2154                          $this->_attributes[$attr_key] = $attr_value[0];
2155                          phpCAS::trace("* " . $attr_key . "=" . $attr_value[0]);
2156                      }
2157                  }
2158                  $result = true;
2159              } else {
2160                  phpCAS::trace("SAML Attributes are empty");
2161                  $result = false;
2162              }
2163          }
2164          phpCAS::traceEnd($result);
2165          return $result;
2166      }

2352      /**
2353       * This method is called by CAS_Client::CAS_Client() when running in callback
2354       * mode. It stores the PGT and its PGT Iou, prints its output and halts.
2355       *
2356       * @return void
2357       */
2358      private function _callback()
2359      {
2360          phpCAS::traceBegin();
2361          if (preg_match('/PGTIOU-[\.\-\w]/', $_GET['pgtIou'])) {
2362              if (preg_match('/[PT]GT-[\.\-\w]/', $_GET['pgtId'])) {
2363                  $this->printHTMLHeader('phpCAS callback');
2364                  $pgt_iou = $_GET['pgtIou'];
2365                  $pgt = $_GET['pgtId'];
2366                  phpCAS::trace('Storing PGT `'.$pgt.'\' (id=`'.$pgt_iou.'\')');
2367                  echo '<p>Storing PGT `'.$pgt.'\' (id=`'.$pgt_iou.'\').</p>';
2368                  $this->_storePGT($pgt, $pgt_iou);
2369                  $this->printHTMLFooter();
2370                  phpCAS::traceExit("Successfull Callback");
2371              } else {
2372                  phpCAS::error('PGT format invalid' . $_GET['pgtId']);
2373                  phpCAS::traceExit('PGT format invalid' . $_GET['pgtId']);
2374              }
2375          } else {
2376              phpCAS::error('PGTiou format invalid' . $_GET['pgtIou']);
2377              phpCAS::traceExit('PGTiou format invalid' . $_GET['pgtIou']);
2378          }
2379  
2380          // Flush the buffer to prevent from sending anything other then a 200
2381          // Success Status back to the CAS Server. The Exception would normally
2382          // report as a 500 error.
2383          flush();
2384          throw new CAS_GracefullTerminationException();
2385      }

2545      // ########################################################################
2546      //  PGT VALIDATION
2547      // ########################################################################
2548      /**
2549      * This method is used to validate a PGT; halt on failure.
2550      *
2551      * @param string &$validate_url the URL of the request to the CAS server.
2552      * @param string $text_response the response of the CAS server, as is
2553      *                              (XML text); result of
2554      *                              CAS_Client::validateCAS10() or
2555      *                              CAS_Client::validateCAS20().
2556      * @param string $tree_response the response of the CAS server, as a DOM XML
2557      * tree; result of CAS_Client::validateCAS10() or CAS_Client::validateCAS20().
2558      *
2559      * @return bool true when successfull and issue a CAS_AuthenticationException
2560      * and false on an error
2561      */
2562      private function _validatePGT(&$validate_url,$text_response,$tree_response)
2563      {
2564          phpCAS::traceBegin();
2565          if ( $tree_response->getElementsByTagName("proxyGrantingTicket")->length == 0) {
2566              phpCAS::trace('<proxyGrantingTicket> not found');
2567              // authentication succeded, but no PGT Iou was transmitted
2568              throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
2569                  $this, 'Ticket validated but no PGT Iou transmitted',
2570                  $validate_url, false/*$no_response*/, false/*$bad_response*/,
2571                  $text_response
2572              );
2573          } else {
2574              // PGT Iou transmitted, extract it
2575              $pgt_iou = trim(
2576                  $tree_response->getElementsByTagName("proxyGrantingTicket")->item(0)->nodeValue
2577              );
2578              if (preg_match('/PGTIOU-[\.\-\w]/', $pgt_iou)) {
2579                  $pgt = $this->_loadPGT($pgt_iou);
2580                  if ( $pgt == false ) {
2581                      phpCAS::trace('could not load PGT');
2582                      throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
2583                          $this,
2584                          'PGT Iou was transmitted but PGT could not be retrieved',
2585                          $validate_url, false/*$no_response*/,
2586                          false/*$bad_response*/, $text_response
2587                      );
2588                  }
2589                  $this->_setPGT($pgt);
2590              } else {
2591                  phpCAS::trace('PGTiou format error');
2592                  throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
2593                      $this, 'PGT Iou was transmitted but has wrong format',
2594                      $validate_url, false/*$no_response*/, false/*$bad_response*/,
2595                      $text_response
2596                  );
2597              }
2598          }
2599          phpCAS::traceEnd(true);
2600          return true;
2601      }
2602  
2603      // ########################################################################
2604      //  PGT VALIDATION
2605      // ########################################################################
2606  
2607      /**
2608       * This method is used to retrieve PT's from the CAS server thanks to a PGT.
2609       *
2610       * @param string $target_service the service to ask for with the PT.
2611       * @param string &$err_code      an error code (PHPCAS_SERVICE_OK on success).
2612       * @param string &$err_msg       an error message (empty on success).
2613       *
2614       * @return a Proxy Ticket, or false on error.
2615       */
2616      public function retrievePT($target_service,&$err_code,&$err_msg)
2617      {
2618          // Argument validation
2619          if (gettype($target_service) != 'string')
2620              throw new CAS_TypeMismatchException($target_service, '$target_service', 'string');
2621  
2622          phpCAS::traceBegin();
2623  
2624          // by default, $err_msg is set empty and $pt to true. On error, $pt is
2625          // set to false and $err_msg to an error message. At the end, if $pt is false
2626          // and $error_msg is still empty, it is set to 'invalid response' (the most
2627          // commonly encountered error).
2628          $err_msg = '';
2629  
2630          // build the URL to retrieve the PT
2631          $cas_url = $this->getServerProxyURL().'?targetService='
2632              .urlencode($target_service).'&pgt='.$this->_getPGT();
2633  
2634          // open and read the URL
2635          if ( !$this->_readURL($cas_url, $headers, $cas_response, $err_msg) ) {
2636              phpCAS::trace(
2637                  'could not open URL \''.$cas_url.'\' to validate ('.$err_msg.')'
2638              );
2639              $err_code = PHPCAS_SERVICE_PT_NO_SERVER_RESPONSE;
2640              $err_msg = 'could not retrieve PT (no response from the CAS server)';
2641              phpCAS::traceEnd(false);
2642              return false;
2643          }
2644  
2645          $bad_response = false;
2646  
2647          if ( !$bad_response ) {
2648              // create new DOMDocument object
2649              $dom = new DOMDocument();
2650              // Fix possible whitspace problems
2651              $dom->preserveWhiteSpace = false;
2652              // read the response of the CAS server into a DOM object
2653              if ( !($dom->loadXML($cas_response))) {
2654                  phpCAS::trace('dom->loadXML() failed');
2655                  // read failed
2656                  $bad_response = true;
2657              }
2658          }
2659  
2660          if ( !$bad_response ) {
2661              // read the root node of the XML tree
2662              if ( !($root = $dom->documentElement) ) {
2663                  phpCAS::trace('documentElement failed');
2664                  // read failed
2665                  $bad_response = true;
2666              }
2667          }
2668  
2669          if ( !$bad_response ) {
2670              // insure that tag name is 'serviceResponse'
2671              if ( $root->localName != 'serviceResponse' ) {
2672                  phpCAS::trace('localName failed');
2673                  // bad root node
2674                  $bad_response = true;
2675              }
2676          }
2677  
2678          if ( !$bad_response ) {
2679              // look for a proxySuccess tag
2680              if ( $root->getElementsByTagName("proxySuccess")->length != 0) {
2681                  $proxy_success_list = $root->getElementsByTagName("proxySuccess");
2682  
2683                  // authentication succeded, look for a proxyTicket tag
2684                  if ( $proxy_success_list->item(0)->getElementsByTagName("proxyTicket")->length != 0) {
2685                      $err_code = PHPCAS_SERVICE_OK;
2686                      $err_msg = '';
2687                      $pt = trim(
2688                          $proxy_success_list->item(0)->getElementsByTagName("proxyTicket")->item(0)->nodeValue
2689                      );
2690                      phpCAS::trace('original PT: '.trim($pt));
2691                      phpCAS::traceEnd($pt);
2692                      return $pt;
2693                  } else {
2694                      phpCAS::trace('<proxySuccess> was found, but not <proxyTicket>');
2695                  }
2696              } else if ($root->getElementsByTagName("proxyFailure")->length != 0) {
2697                  // look for a proxyFailure tag
2698                  $proxy_failure_list = $root->getElementsByTagName("proxyFailure");
2699  
2700                  // authentication failed, extract the error
2701                  $err_code = PHPCAS_SERVICE_PT_FAILURE;
2702                  $err_msg = 'PT retrieving failed (code=`'
2703                  .$proxy_failure_list->item(0)->getAttribute('code')
2704                  .'\', message=`'
2705                  .trim($proxy_failure_list->item(0)->nodeValue)
2706                  .'\')';
2707                  phpCAS::traceEnd(false);
2708                  return false;
2709              } else {
2710                  phpCAS::trace('neither <proxySuccess> nor <proxyFailure> found');
2711              }
2712          }
2713  
2714          // at this step, we are sure that the response of the CAS server was
2715          // illformed
2716          $err_code = PHPCAS_SERVICE_PT_BAD_SERVER_RESPONSE;
2717          $err_msg = 'Invalid response from the CAS server (response=`'
2718              .$cas_response.'\')';
2719  
2720          phpCAS::traceEnd(false);
2721          return false;
2722      }

2735      /**

2737       *
2738       * @param string $url      the URL to access.
2739       * @param string &$headers an array containing the HTTP header lines of the
2740       * response (an empty array on failure).
2741       * @param string &$body    the body of the response, as a string (empty on
2742       * failure).
2743       * @param string &$err_msg an error message, filled on failure.
2744       *
2745       * @return true on success, false otherwise (in this later case, $err_msg
2746       * contains an error message).
2747       */
2748      private function _readURL($url, &$headers, &$body, &$err_msg)
2749      {
2750          phpCAS::traceBegin();
2751          $className = $this->_requestImplementation;
2752          $request = new $className();
2753  
2754          if (count($this->_curl_options)) {
2755              $request->setCurlOptions($this->_curl_options);
2756          }
2757  
2758          $request->setUrl($url);
2759  
2760          if (empty($this->_cas_server_ca_cert) && !$this->_no_cas_server_validation) {
2761              phpCAS::error(
2762                  'one of the methods phpCAS::setCasServerCACert() or phpCAS::setNoCasServerValidation() must be called.'
2763              );
2764          }
2765          if ($this->_cas_server_ca_cert != '') {
2766              $request->setSslCaCert(
2767                  $this->_cas_server_ca_cert, $this->_cas_server_cn_validate
2768              );
2769          }
2770  
2771          // add extra stuff if SAML
2772          if ($this->getServerVersion() == SAML_VERSION_1_1) {
2773              $request->addHeader("soapaction: http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/security");
2774              $request->addHeader("cache-control: no-cache");
2775              $request->addHeader("pragma: no-cache");
2776              $request->addHeader("accept: text/xml");
2777              $request->addHeader("connection: keep-alive");
2778              $request->addHeader("content-type: text/xml");
2779              $request->makePost();
2780              $request->setPostBody($this->_buildSAMLPayload());
2781          }
2782  
2783          if ($request->send()) {
2784              $headers = $request->getResponseHeaders();
2785              $body = $request->getResponseBody();
2786              $err_msg = '';
2787              phpCAS::traceEnd(true);
2788              return true;
2789          } else {
2790              $headers = '';
2791              $body = '';
2792              $err_msg = $request->getErrorMessage();
2793              phpCAS::traceEnd(false);
2794              return false;
2795          }
2796      }

2800       *
2801       * @return the SOAP-encased SAMLP artifact (the ticket).
2802       */
2803      private function _buildSAMLPayload()
2804      {
2805          phpCAS::traceBegin();

2807          //get the ticket

2813  
2814          phpCAS::traceEnd($body);
2815          return ($body);

2830      /**
2831       * Answer a proxy-authenticated service handler.
2832       *
2833       * @param string $type The service type. One of:
2834       * PHPCAS_PROXIED_SERVICE_HTTP_GET, PHPCAS_PROXIED_SERVICE_HTTP_POST,
2835       * PHPCAS_PROXIED_SERVICE_IMAP
2836       *
2837       * @return CAS_ProxiedService
2838       * @throws InvalidArgumentException If the service type is unknown.
2839       */
2840      public function getProxiedService ($type)
2841      {
2842          // Sequence validation
2843          $this->ensureIsProxy();
2844          $this->ensureAuthenticationCallSuccessful();
2845  
2846          // Argument validation
2847          if (gettype($type) != 'string')
2848              throw new CAS_TypeMismatchException($type, '$type', 'string');
2849  
2850          switch ($type) {
2851          case PHPCAS_PROXIED_SERVICE_HTTP_GET:
2852          case PHPCAS_PROXIED_SERVICE_HTTP_POST:
2853              $requestClass = $this->_requestImplementation;
2854              $request = new $requestClass();
2855              if (count($this->_curl_options)) {
2856                  $request->setCurlOptions($this->_curl_options);
2857              }
2858              $proxiedService = new $type($request, $this->_serviceCookieJar);
2859              if ($proxiedService instanceof CAS_ProxiedService_Testable) {
2860                  $proxiedService->setCasClient($this);
2861              }
2862              return $proxiedService;
2863          case PHPCAS_PROXIED_SERVICE_IMAP;
2864              $proxiedService = new CAS_ProxiedService_Imap($this->_getUser());
2865              if ($proxiedService instanceof CAS_ProxiedService_Testable) {
2866                  $proxiedService->setCasClient($this);
2867              }
2868              return $proxiedService;
2869          default:
2870              throw new CAS_InvalidArgumentException(
2871                  "Unknown proxied-service type, $type."
2872              );
2873          }
2874      }

2876      /**
2877       * Initialize a proxied-service handler with the proxy-ticket it should use.
2878       *
2879       * @param CAS_ProxiedService $proxiedService service handler
2880       *
2881       * @return void
2882       *
2883       * @throws CAS_ProxyTicketException If there is a proxy-ticket failure.
2884       *        The code of the Exception will be one of:
2885       *            PHPCAS_SERVICE_PT_NO_SERVER_RESPONSE
2886       *            PHPCAS_SERVICE_PT_BAD_SERVER_RESPONSE
2887       *            PHPCAS_SERVICE_PT_FAILURE
2888       * @throws CAS_ProxiedService_Exception If there is a failure getting the
2889       * url from the proxied service.
2890       */
2891      public function initializeProxiedService (CAS_ProxiedService $proxiedService)
2892      {
2893          // Sequence validation
2894          $this->ensureIsProxy();
2895          $this->ensureAuthenticationCallSuccessful();
2896  
2897          $url = $proxiedService->getServiceUrl();
2898          if (!is_string($url)) {
2899              throw new CAS_ProxiedService_Exception(
2900                  "Proxied Service ".get_class($proxiedService)
2901                  ."->getServiceUrl() should have returned a string, returned a "
2902                  .gettype($url)." instead."
2903              );
2904          }
2905          $pt = $this->retrievePT($url, $err_code, $err_msg);
2906          if (!$pt) {
2907              throw new CAS_ProxyTicketException($err_msg, $err_code);
2908          }
2909          $proxiedService->setProxyTicket($pt);
2910      }

2917       * PHPCAS_SERVICE_OK (on success), PHPCAS_SERVICE_PT_NO_SERVER_RESPONSE,
2918       * PHPCAS_SERVICE_PT_BAD_SERVER_RESPONSE, PHPCAS_SERVICE_PT_FAILURE,

2931
