3112      /**
3113       * This method is used to validate a cas 2.0 ST or PT; halt on failure
3114       * Used for all CAS 2.0 validations
3115       *
3116       * @param string &$validate_url  the url of the reponse
3117       * @param string &$text_response the text of the repsones
3118       * @param string &$tree_response the domxml tree of the respones
3119       * @param bool   $renew          true to force the authentication with the CAS server
3120       *
3121       * @return bool true when successfull and issue a CAS_AuthenticationException
3122       * and false on an error
3123       */
3124      public function validateCAS20(&$validate_url,&$text_response,&$tree_response, $renew=false)
3125      {
3126          phpCAS::traceBegin();
3127          phpCAS::trace($text_response);
3128          $result = false;
3129          // build the URL to validate the ticket
3130          if ($this->getAllowedProxyChains()->isProxyingAllowed()) {
3131              $validate_url = $this->getServerProxyValidateURL().'&ticket='
3132                  .urlencode($this->getTicket());
3133          } else {
3134              $validate_url = $this->getServerServiceValidateURL().'&ticket='
3135                  .urlencode($this->getTicket());
3136          }
3137  
3138          if ( $this->isProxy() ) {
3139              // pass the callback url for CAS proxies
3140              $validate_url .= '&pgtUrl='.urlencode($this->_getCallbackURL());
3141          }
3142  
3143          if ( $renew ) {
3144              // pass the renew

3145              $validate_url .= '&renew=true';
3146          }
3147  
3148          // open and read the URL
3149          if ( !$this->_readURL($validate_url, $headers, $text_response, $err_msg) ) {
3150              phpCAS::trace(
3151                  'could not open URL \''.$validate_url.'\' to validate ('.$err_msg.')'
3152              );
3153              throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
3154                  $this, 'Ticket not validated', $validate_url,
3155                  true/*$no_response*/
3156              );
3157              $result = false;
3158          }
3159  
3160          // create new DOMDocument object
3161          $dom = new DOMDocument();
3162          // Fix possible whitspace problems
3163          $dom->preserveWhiteSpace = false;
3164          // CAS servers should only return data in utf-8
3165          $dom->encoding = "utf-8";
3166          // read the response of the CAS server into a DOMDocument object
3167          if ( !($dom->loadXML($text_response))) {
3168              // read failed
3169              throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
3170                  $this, 'Ticket not validated', $validate_url,
3171                  false/*$no_response*/, true/*$bad_response*/, $text_response
3172              );
3173              $result = false;
3174          } else if ( !($tree_response = $dom->documentElement) ) {
3175              // read the root node of the XML tree
3176              // read failed
3177              throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
3178                  $this, 'Ticket not validated', $validate_url,
3179                  false/*$no_response*/, true/*$bad_response*/, $text_response
3180              );
3181              $result = false;
3182          } else if ($tree_response->localName != 'serviceResponse') {
3183              // insure that tag name is 'serviceResponse'
3184              // bad root node
3185              throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
3186                  $this, 'Ticket not validated', $validate_url,
3187                  false/*$no_response*/, true/*$bad_response*/, $text_response
3188              );
3189              $result = false;
3190          } else if ($tree_response->getElementsByTagName("authenticationSuccess")->length != 0) {
3191              // authentication succeded, extract the user name
3192              $success_elements = $tree_response
3193                  ->getElementsByTagName("authenticationSuccess");
3194              if ( $success_elements->item(0)->getElementsByTagName("user")->length == 0) {
3195                  // no user specified => error
3196                  throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
3197                      $this, 'Ticket not validated', $validate_url,
3198                      false/*$no_response*/, true/*$bad_response*/, $text_response
3199                  );
3200                  $result = false;
3201              } else {
3202                  $this->_setUser(
3203                      trim(
3204                          $success_elements->item(0)->getElementsByTagName("user")->item(0)->nodeValue
3205                      )
3206                  );
3207                  $this->_readExtraAttributesCas20($success_elements);
3208                  // Store the proxies we are sitting behind for authorization checking
3209                  $proxyList = array();
3210                  if ( sizeof($arr = $success_elements->item(0)->getElementsByTagName("proxy")) > 0) {
3211                      foreach ($arr as $proxyElem) {
3212                          phpCAS::trace("Found Proxy: ".$proxyElem->nodeValue);
3213                          $proxyList[] = trim($proxyElem->nodeValue);
3214                      }
3215                      $this->_setProxies($proxyList);
3216                      phpCAS::trace("Storing Proxy List");
3217                  }
3218                  // Check if the proxies in front of us are allowed
3219                  if (!$this->getAllowedProxyChains()->isProxyListAllowed($proxyList)) {
3220                      throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
3221                          $this, 'Proxy not allowed', $validate_url,
3222                          false/*$no_response*/, true/*$bad_response*/,
3223                          $text_response
3224                      );
3225                      $result = false;
3226                  } else {
3227                      $result = true;
3228                  }
3229              }
3230          } else if ( $tree_response->getElementsByTagName("authenticationFailure")->length != 0) {
3231              // authentication succeded, extract the error code and message
3232              $auth_fail_list = $tree_response
3233                  ->getElementsByTagName("authenticationFailure");
3234              throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
3235                  $this, 'Ticket not validated', $validate_url,
3236                  false/*$no_response*/, false/*$bad_response*/,
3237                  $text_response,
3238                  $auth_fail_list->item(0)->getAttribute('code')/*$err_code*/,
3239                  trim($auth_fail_list->item(0)->nodeValue)/*$err_msg*/
3240              );
3241              $result = false;
3242          } else {
3243              throw new CAS_AuthenticationException(
3244                  $this, 'Ticket not validated', $validate_url,
3245                  false/*$no_response*/, true/*$bad_response*/,
3246                  $text_response
3247              );
3248              $result = false;
3249          }
3250          if ($result) {
3251              $this->_renameSession($this->getTicket());
3252          }
3253          // at this step, Ticket has been validated and $this->_user has been set,
3254  
3255          phpCAS::traceEnd($result);
3256          return $result;
3257      }

3260      /**
3261       * This method will parse the DOM and pull out the attributes from the XML

3269      private function _readExtraAttributesCas20($success_elements)
3270      {
3271          phpCAS::traceBegin();
3272  
3273          $extra_attributes = array();
3274  
3275          // "Jasig Style" Attributes:
3276          //
3277          //     <cas:serviceResponse xmlns:cas='http://www.yale.edu/tp/cas'>
3278          //         <cas:authenticationSuccess>
3279          //             <cas:user>jsmith</cas:user>
3280          //             <cas:attributes>

3288          //         </cas:authenticationSuccess>
3289          //     </cas:serviceResponse>
3290          //
3291          if ( $success_elements->item(0)->getElementsByTagName("attributes")->length != 0) {
3292              $attr_nodes = $success_elements->item(0)
3293                  ->getElementsByTagName("attributes");
3294              phpCas :: trace("Found nested jasig style attributes");
3295              if ($attr_nodes->item(0)->hasChildNodes()) {
3296                  // Nested Attributes
3297                  foreach ($attr_nodes->item(0)->childNodes as $attr_child) {
3298                      phpCas :: trace(
3299                          "Attribute [".$attr_child->localName."] = "
3300                          .$attr_child->nodeValue
3301                      );
3302                      $this->_addAttributeToArray(
3303                          $extra_attributes, $attr_child->localName,
3304                          $attr_child->nodeValue
3305                      );
3306                  }
3307              }
3308          } else {
3309              // "RubyCAS Style" attributes
3310              //
3311              //     <cas:serviceResponse xmlns:cas='http://www.yale.edu/tp/cas'>
3312              //         <cas:authenticationSuccess>
3313              //             <cas:user>jsmith</cas:user>
3314              //
3315              //             <cas:attraStyle>RubyCAS</cas:attraStyle>
3316              //             <cas:surname>Smith</cas:surname>
3317              //             <cas:givenName>John</cas:givenName>
3318              //             <cas:memberOf>CN=Staff,OU=Groups,DC=example,DC=edu</cas:memberOf>
3319              //             <cas:memberOf>CN=Spanish Department,OU=Departments,OU=Groups,DC=example,DC=edu</cas:memberOf>
3320              //
3321              //             <cas:proxyGrantingTicket>PGTIOU-84678-8a9d2sfa23casd</cas:proxyGrantingTicket>
3322              //         </cas:authenticationSuccess>
3323              //     </cas:serviceResponse>
3324              //
3325              phpCas :: trace("Testing for rubycas style attributes");
3326              $childnodes = $success_elements->item(0)->childNodes;
3327              foreach ($childnodes as $attr_node) {
3328                  switch ($attr_node->localName) {
3329                  case 'user':
3330                  case 'proxies':
3331                  case 'proxyGrantingTicket':
3332                      continue;
3333                  default:

3340                              $attr_node->nodeValue
3341                          );

3347          // "Name-Value" attributes.
3348          //
3349          // Attribute format from these mailing list thread:
3350          // http://jasig.275507.n4.nabble.com/CAS-attributes-and-how-they-appear-in-the-CAS-response-td264272.html
3351          // Note: This is a less widely used format, but in use by at least two institutions.
3352          //
3353          //     <cas:serviceResponse xmlns:cas='http://www.yale.edu/tp/cas'>
3354          //         <cas:authenticationSuccess>
3355          //             <cas:user>jsmith</cas:user>
3356          //
3357          //             <cas:attribute name='attraStyle' value='Name-Value' />

3365          //     </cas:serviceResponse>

3367          if (!count($extra_attributes)

3369          ) {
3370              $attr_nodes = $success_elements->item(0)

3372              $firstAttr = $attr_nodes->item(0);
3373              if (!$firstAttr->hasChildNodes()

3375                  && $firstAttr->hasAttribute('value')
3376              ) {

3379                  foreach ($attr_nodes as $attr_node) {
3380                      if ($attr_node->hasAttribute('name')
3381                          && $attr_node->hasAttribute('value')

3388                              $extra_attributes, $attr_node->getAttribute('name'),
3389                              $attr_node->getAttribute('value')
3390                          );
3391                      }
3392                  }
3393              }
3394          }

3396          $this->setAttributes($extra_attributes);
3397          phpCAS::traceEnd();

3467      /**
3468       * This method returns the URL of the current request (without any ticket
3469       * CGI parameter).
3470       *
3471       * @return The URL
3472       */
3473      public function getURL()
3474      {
3475          phpCAS::traceBegin();
3476          // the URL is built when needed only
3477          if ( empty($this->_url) ) {
3478              $final_uri = '';
3479              // remove the ticket if present in the URL
3480              $final_uri = ($this->_isHttps()) ? 'https' : 'http';
3481              $final_uri .= '://';
3482  
3483              $final_uri .= $this->_getClientUrl();
3484              $request_uri    = explode('?', $_SERVER['REQUEST_URI'], 2);
3485              $final_uri        .= $request_uri[0];
3486  
3487              if (isset($request_uri[1]) && $request_uri[1]) {
3488                  $query_string= $this->_removeParameterFromQueryString('ticket', $request_uri[1]);
3489  
3490                  // If the query string still has anything left,
3491                  // append it to the final URI
3492                  if ($query_string !== '') {
3493                      $final_uri    .= "?$query_string";
3494                  }
3495              }
3496  
3497              phpCAS::trace("Final URI: $final_uri");
3498              $this->setURL($final_uri);
3499          }
3500          phpCAS::traceEnd($this->_url);
3501          return $this->_url;

3505      /**
3506       * Try to figure out the phpCas client URL with possible Proxys / Ports etc.
3507       *
3508       * @return string Server URL with domain:port
3509       */
3510      private function _getClientUrl()
3511      {
3512          $server_url = '';
3513          if (!empty($_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_HOST'])) {
3514              // explode the host list separated by comma and use the first host
3515              $hosts = explode(',', $_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_HOST']);
3516              // see rfc7239#5.3 and rfc7230#2.7.1: port is in HTTP_X_FORWARDED_HOST if non default
3517              return $hosts[0];
3518          } else if (!empty($_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_SERVER'])) {
3519              $server_url = $_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_SERVER'];
3520          } else {
3521              if (empty($_SERVER['SERVER_NAME'])) {
3522                  $server_url = $_SERVER['HTTP_HOST'];
3523              } else {
3524                  $server_url = $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME'];
3525              }
3526          }
3527          if (!strpos($server_url, ':')) {
3528              if (empty($_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_PORT'])) {
3529                  $server_port = $_SERVER['SERVER_PORT'];
3530              } else {
3531                  $ports = explode(',', $_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_PORT']);
3532                  $server_port = $ports[0];
3533              }
3534  
3535              if ( ($this->_isHttps() && $server_port!=443)
3536                  || (!$this->_isHttps() && $server_port!=80)
3537              ) {
3538                  $server_url .= ':';
3539                  $server_url .= $server_port;
3540              }
3541          }
3542          return $server_url;
3543      }

3545      /**
3546       * This method checks to see if the request is secured via HTTPS
3547       *
3548       * @return bool true if https, false otherwise
3549       */
3550      private function _isHttps()
3551      {
3552          if (!empty($_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_PROTO'])) {
3553              return ($_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_PROTO'] === 'https');
3554          }
3555          if ( isset($_SERVER['HTTPS'])
3556              && !empty($_SERVER['HTTPS'])
3557              && strcasecmp($_SERVER['HTTPS'], 'off') !== 0
3558          ) {
3559              return true;
3560          } else {
3561              return false;
3562          }
3563      }

3565      /**
3566       * Removes a parameter from a query string
3567       *
3568       * @param string $parameterName name of parameter
3569       * @param string $queryString   query string
3570       *
3571       * @return string new query string
3572       *

3788       * @param int $type type of rebroadcasting.
